---

## What is this?

A self-hosted, modular operating system for AI agents — with a Life Planner as its first real module. It lives on Pauly's existing KVM2 VPS (always-on) with overflow to KVM4 and OpenRouter for heavier jobs.

It is **not** another chatbot wrapper. It's an orchestration layer that manages agents, routes work to the right model, remembers everything, and gives Pauly a single place to plan his life and run autonomous tasks.

---

## Why build it?

1. **Tool sprawl** — Too many disconnected AI tools, each starting from zero context every time.
2. **No memory** — Agents don't remember who Pauly is, what he's working on, or what they did last session.
3. **Lost outputs** — Things get built, then forgotten in random folders.
4. **No autonomy** — Nothing runs unless Pauly is sitting in front of it.
5. **Life admin is scattered** — Tasks, habits, calendar, and goals live in different apps that don't talk to each other.

---

## Core design decisions

| Decision | Choice | Why |
|----------|--------|-----|
| **Architecture** | Orchestrator-first, planning is module #1 | Avoids rebuilding when agents outgrow a bolted-on system |
| **Orchestrator spine** | Formalized from existing `loop-and-delegate` + `agent-resource-guard` skills | Reuses proven logic, doesn't start from scratch |
| **Data split** | Local Postgres (KVM2) for sensitive/agent logs + Supabase for tasks/calendar/habits | Private stuff stays private, plannable stuff syncs to any device |
| **Model routing** | Tag-based: `routine` → cheap/local/free, `legal` or `important` → Claude/Gemini | Token-conscious by default, smart when it matters |
| **Chat/capture** | Conduit (Matrix, self-hosted on KVM2) | Private, lightweight, replaces Telegram/Slack for personal capture |
| **Dashboard** | PWA, iPad-first | One tab, works offline, quick-add widget |
| **Auth** | Traefik basic auth + passkey | Simple, secure enough for single-user VPS |
| **Fun factor** | All of it — gamification, personality, voice-first, good aesthetics | Cheap local model handles banter; expensive model only for real reasoning |

