## What it does (Module 1 — Life Planner)

### Task management
- Inbox for quick capture (via Matrix chat or dashboard widget)
- Voice capture → faster-whisper transcription → auto-creates task
- Tasks have tags, priorities, due dates
- Kanban view on dashboard

### Calendar
- Syncs with Google Calendar (connector already exists)
- Events and tasks visible together on the dashboard

### Habits & streaks
- Define recurring habits
- Track streaks, earn XP
- Visible progress on dashboard (not buried in a menu)

### Gamification
- XP system tied to task completion and habit streaks
- Levels / milestones (keeps it motivating, not patronising)
- Rendered on dashboard — not a separate app

### Voice-first
- Talk to it via Matrix or dashboard mic button
- faster-whisper (already running on KVM2) handles transcription
- Supports quick capture, task creation, and basic agent commands

---

## What the orchestrator does (the spine)

### Agent registry
- Each agent is a named entry with: what model it uses, what it's good at, what tools it has access to, its personality/voice profile
- New agents plug in without rebuilding anything

### Job queue
- Tasks (from life planner or ad-hoc) get queued
- Orchestrator assigns to the right agent based on tags and routing rules
- Jobs can run autonomously (no human in the loop) or require approval

### Model router
- Rules engine: match task tags → model
- Default: cheapest model that can do the job
- Override: `legal-case`, `important`, or manual flag → Claude / Gemini
- Tracks token usage per agent, per job

### Memory
- Agents read/write to a shared context store (local Postgres)
- Outputs auto-saved and indexed (no more lost work)
- Legal/sensitive data never leaves KVM2

